    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🔥 Smoky Baingan Bharta Recipe</h1>
      

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>2 large Eggplants (Baingan)</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Oil</li>
            <li>1 Onion (finely chopped)</li>
            <li>2 Tomatoes (chopped)</li>
            <li>4 Garlic Cloves (minced)</li>
            <li>1 Green Chili (chopped)</li>
            <li>½ tsp Turmeric Powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp Red Chili Powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
            <li>½ tsp Garam Masala</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Coriander Leaves (chopped)</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Roast the eggplants directly over an open flame or in an oven until the skin is charred.</li>
            <li>Peel off the burnt skin and mash the pulp.</li>
            <li>Heat oil in a pan and add cumin seeds.</li>
            <li>Add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add garlic, green chilies, and tomatoes. Cook until soft.</li>
            <li>Mix in turmeric, red chili powder, and salt.</li>
            <li>Add the mashed eggplant and mix well.</li>
            <li>Cook for 5-7 minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>
            <li>Finish with garam masala and coriander leaves.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with roti, naan, or rice.</li>
        </ol>
